post_text:
It's game day! Come out and cheer on your GM Boys Basketball team in their home opener vs. Southland. Game time 7:15 Varsity, 6pm JV. This is the first official event in the new gym and facilities--GO SUPERLARKS!!!!

**Some info on the new gym: The first evening event will be a Boys Basketball game on Tuesday, December 13th. We will want people to enter the gymnasium at the West Entrance of the new addition. (Door W3) There is a ticket booth immediately to the left as you enter the facility in the lobby area to purchase tickets and pick up a program. Due to the generosity of the various booster clubs, the middle area of the home side bleachers have backs on them. The school would like to let the senior citizens and veterans know that the bottom two rows of the home section with bleacher backs are reserved for you if you choose to sit in those areas. Seating in the new gymnasium is roughly twice the capacity of the gym in the dome. The Home side is on the South and the visitor side is on the North.

There's still time to get your tickets for Donkey Basketball!!! We have a limited number left to sell so get yours now. Tickets can be purchased at Glynn's Motor Mart, by contacting Jennifer Johnson Cotten at 507-269-8699, from any GM Boys Booster club member (Lisa Massmann Glynn, Pam Stevens, Sara Warmka, Diane Monson Jech, Lynn Baldus, or Bob Burmester), or by sending us a message here. Tickets are $10 in advance, or $12 at the door if there are any left available.

Remember we are also having a tailgating supper before the game from 5-7pm in the cafetorium, featuring Pulled pork sandwich, drink, and chips or bar all for only $5.

Come out for a great time and grab a bite before the game, all while supporting the GM Boys Basketball program. See you there!
